    [
      "A)Condition for StartUp :-\n1] At Start of shift /End of shift\n2] Model &/or Set up change\n3] Pokayoke Failure, corrected & production resumed\n4] If poka yoke bypassed and production continued as per alternate poka yoke bypass document\n5] More than 4 hour Planned shut down\n6) During Abnormal Situations (6a-Emergency Alarm / 6b-Power Failure / 6c-Machine or Tool Breakdown - more than 45 mins / 6d-Inspection Guage or Instrument breakdown or fallen down)\nB)Reactivity Rule:- If any NC is found inform to CC/ Shift Incharge , Initiate actions for correction & After closure of NC treat the shift as a fresh shift , Start checking from the begining of the check points in the next column."
    ]
  ]
